text:
There is an experimental fix to address a leakage Apache Axis has encountered,
one that is O(n-ant-or-antcall-tasks); things like properties in the task
probably just scales the damage.

it will be in the nightly build, but you are better off just getting CVS access
and building it yourself. That way you get to make sure the optional libraries
you need are in there; nightly builds are very sparse
creator: stevel@apache.org
gregm@bea.com
bodewig@apache.org
text:
The change looks fine at first glance, we'll see whether it has some ill effects
during testing I hope (a side effect of property using the project member
is possible).

I'll look into Property to make sure we'll not end up with NPEs and commit your
patch, it will be in the nightly builds of 2002-09-14 (not earlier).

creator: bodewig@apache.org
text:

it should get us further.
